The Oswego County Comets wanted to make the presentation of the Maggie Sue Glenister Wilcox scholarship special for the two seniors since it has been a tough year for the students. Good morning! Those who will be participating in our Summer Meal Program are asked to sign up by Thursday, July 2! Forms are located below and can be found in Word/PDF form via our Food Services page on the right hand side under 'Quick Links': https://www.mexicocsd.org/domain/47

Also attached is the Notification of SFSP Site and Meal Availability:

Regardless of whether the school district is providing a SFSP, every school district is responsible to ensure that information regarding meal accessibility is provided in ways ensured to reach families in need in their identified preferred language. School districts must cooperate with SFSP sponsors to distribute materials and provide outreach to inform families of the availability and location of free SFSP meals for students over the summer.

Families can be provided the following information to quickly and easily find summer meals near them.

post_text:
Here's today's workout from Mr. Parkhurst to try. Feel free to modified the intervals to make workout shorter or longer.

Format: Start with exercise 1. Then do 1 + 2. Then do 1 + 2 + 3.. all the way to 10!

30 seconds on, 15 off with no added breaks! (takes about 45 minutes, if you change to :20 on, :10 off will be about 30 minutes).
¬∑ Squat jumps
¬∑ 4 x shoulder tap with 1 push-up
¬∑ Burpees
¬∑ Commandos (switch halfway or alternate)
¬∑ Jumping lunges
¬∑ Pike ups
¬∑ Jumping jacks
¬∑ Triceps dips
¬∑ Burpee with 2 jump lunges
¬∑ Squat jacks

#TriviaTuesday Question of the Day: The complete mural "La Guerre d'Independence" exists in the foyer of the Mexico High School. Where is the only other location where the complete mural can be viewed?

ANSWER:
C. The White House in Washington, D.C.

From Mr. Emery: The version that exists there, however, is not set in one room as 10 panels are in a reception area while 22 panels are in a dining room.

See you again next Tuesday for more trivia!

post_text:
Question of the day: What was the original name for the school that was incorporated by special act of the New York State legislature in 1826?
A. Mexico Union Free School
B. Rensselaer Oswego Academy
C. Central Oswego County Academy
D. Mexico Military Academy

ANSWER: Looks like we stumped quite a few of you -- the answer is B! From Mr. Emery: "Rensselaer Oswego Academy - the Rensselaer was after Stephen VanRensselaer, a patron of education who the locals thought might donate money to school. He never did!"

Thanks for playing along, we will have another question for you next week!

post_text:
#MindfulMonday: Today‚Äôs suggestion from the Middle School PE staff is to take a nature walk outside! Leave your phone OFF and avoid talking or other distractions and take some time to reflect when you get home.

Questions to consider:
How did you feel before, during and after your walk? Did anything change?
What was the most interesting thing you saw, smelled, heard? What made it interesting?
What other emotions did you feel on your walk?

FACT: Walking improves your mood, lowers stress and anxiety, provides a sense of purpose and best of all gets you moving!! Now get outside and enjoy!

post_text: This looks like a fun one! Thanks for the daily challenges, Mr. Fellows!
shared_text:
Galen Fellows
March 25 at 12:48 PM ¬∑

Challenge #6
Today‚Äôs challenge is to build a car that operates using only the weight of a falling object to move forward. Materials will completely depend on what you have available, but things like straws, popsicle sticks, bottle caps, old cds, peanut butter jar lids, cardboard, tissue boxes, string, fishing weights are a few suggestions to get your creative juices running.

Novice: Build the device. If you‚Äôre stuck on what materials you could use a quick google search for gravity-powered vehicle and checking out some of the supplies people have used should kickstart things.

Intermediate: Use gear / pulley ratios to get the car to move forward VERY slowly, then reverse things to go VERY fast.

Advanced: Design your device to be multi-stage and be able to move forward to a set distance, trigger a mechanism and then move back toward your starting position.

post_text: Check out today's challenge from Mr. Fellows! When you build one, send us a video so we can share it!!
shared_text:
Galen Fellows
March 20 at 12:14 PM ¬∑

Stuck inside in the rain
Challenge #3
Since the rain is keeping us inside, we might as well have a lengthier project for indoors. Taking inspiration from Tracey Reynolds it‚Äôs time to setup a Rube Goldberg machine that runs throughout your house.
Note: Kids (including grown-up kids like myself) you most definitely have to clean up your device so that you don‚Äôt feel the ire of the rest of the household.
Novice: Make it work using only one input (unless you make yourself part of the device).
Intermediate: Additionally, label all of the simple machines on your device. Include at least one inclined plane, 1st class lever, 2nd class lever, 3rd class lever, screw, wheel and axle, pulley, and wedge.
Advanced: Also, identify all of the sources of stored energy. Include at least one gravitational, elastic, chemical, and electrical.

Let your inner child run wild this weekend!

Some of my favorite large-scale examples of Rube Goldberg Machines:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z57kGB-mI54
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qybUFnY7Y8w

ADVENTURE: Ms. Nicosia from the HS Library went exploring and came across a shipwreck that has recently washed ashore near Sandy Pond!

Experts say they are the remains of the three-masted schooner Hartford that sank on Oct. 11, 1894, more than 125 years ago. READ more about the ship and its discovery: http://www.oswegocountynewsnow.com/news/long-lost-shipwreck-washes-ashore-near-sandy-pond/article_8db140ee-69eb-11ea-a3e4-fbc34fcd22f9.html

post_text:
Good afternoon,

This is Mexico Superintendent of Schools Sean Bruno. In an effort to maintain continuity of learning for your children, our teachers have created packets of educational activities. These materials, along with information about student meal plans, are now ready for delivery by our bus drivers.

Packets for students in grades Pre-K-4 will be delivered on Wednesday, March 18 between 9 a.m. and 2 p.m.

Packets for students in grades 5-12 will be delivered on Thursday, March 19 between 9 a.m. and 2 p.m.

In the event that you are not home at the time of delivery, these packets will be left at your home.

For some students, we will also be delivering their laptops and/ or musical instruments. Someone must be home to sign for receipt of these items. If you are not home to sign for these, we will leave you a note with further instructions for pick-up or delivery.

Thank you,

Sean C. Bruno
Superintendent of Schools

CONGRATULATIONS: Our Vex Robotics teams competed this past weekend in Baldwinsville! Team 1757U ranked third after the qualification rounds with a 6-1-1 record, and 1757A earned the Judge's Award with a bot that expanded to cover the whole arena! Great work!

They will compete at the largest statewide competition in the country on Feb. 29 at the Syracuse Oncenter from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m.!

TOMORROW: On Tuesday 1/14, the boys varsity swimming & diving team is taking on J-D/CBA at 5 p.m. at home!

In 2018, the teams swam to a 93-93 tie and last year, J-D/CBA took it 93-92 in a meet that came down to the last relay. This year is shaping up to be much of the same with the Tigers coming in at 6-3 and JD/CBA 5-3 on the season, sharing loses to the same 3 teams (Liverpool, Baldwinsville, & Fulton).

This will be JD/CBA‚Äôs first away meet of the season, let‚Äôs pack the stands and make it a true home pool environment! Asking for all fans to wear BLACK, let‚Äôs make this meet a BLACK OUT! Go TIGERS!

Good morning,

This is Superintendent Sean Bruno of Mexico Central Schools. Due to weather conditions in the majority of our district, we are closing early today, 12/18/19. The high school will dismiss at 12:30; MS at 12:45 and the elementary schools at 1:30.

There will be no afternoon pre-K, BOCES or other after school or evening activities. The MS band and chorus concert is canceled, and Friday morning's rescheduled performance will be streamed online for all parents to watch.

Thank you and have a safe afternoon.

post_text:
AWESOME WORK: The Vex Robotics season is officially in full swing as 13 of our team members representing our two teams competed against 21 teams at Fowler for the first competition this year.

Team 1757A made up of returning members from last season ranked fifth after a grueling day of ups and downs and allied with the team from Rome Free Academy to take home the championship trophy! Team 1757U made entirely of new members to our team ranked sixth after starting the day without a fully functional bot and put up an amazing set of performances over the course of the day. Each team ended with five wins and two losses!

Each team ended with five wins and two losses!

post_text: HOLY COW: Yesterday, several of our HS students took a field trip to three locations in Oswego County to learn about Agricultural careers that are available locally and require various levels of education from a high school diploma to a doctorate. Thank you to Behling's Orchard, Wilkholm Dairy and the 1886 Malt House for opening their doors to us!
